<h2>How to Design a Link-Worthy Study</h2>
<p>The research design determines whether journalists cite your work or ignore it. Follow this process.</p>
<h3>Step 1: Find a Data Gap</h3>
<p>Identify questions in your industry that lack current data. Writers need fresh statistics. Old data gets cited less.</p>
<p><strong>Gap identification methods:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Review industry reports from the past year. Note outdated statistics.</li>
<li>Search Google Scholar for recent research. Identify missing topics.</li>
<li>Survey your customers about unanswered questions.</li>
<li>Analyze competitor content for missing data.</li>
<li>Review Reddit, forums, and social media for recurring questions.</li>
</ul>
